13:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Codium AI and Cursor share a solid foundation of core features including Code Review, Debugging, Test Generation, Multi Language. Where Codium AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ide Integration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Cursor uniquely offers Autocomplete and Code Generation and Refactoring and Chat and Documentation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Codium AI holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Cursor scores 9/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Codium AI offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $19/mo, compared to Cursor's starting price of $20/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Codium AI's free tier and Cursor's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
