17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Codium AI is best suited for teams prioritizing test coverage, quality focused development, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Cursor, meanwhile, shines for developers wanting an AI native editor, rapid prototyping, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Codium AI describes itself as \"AI-generated tests and code integrity analysis.\" Cursor, established in 2023, positions itself as \"The AI-first code editor built for productivity.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Cursor** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 5), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Codium AI is a poor choice — far from it. Codium AI excels in its own right, particularly for teams prioritizing test coverage and quality focused development.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value purpose-built ai editor experience, go with Cursor. If excellent test generation matters more to you, Codium AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
